BMEDN_Learning Outcomes_ENG 1.  |  Major Programme:
Graduates from this Progamme will have
acquired
(1)  |  sufficient mathematics knowledge of
mathematical analysis, linear algebra, computer programming for mathematics,
and further knowledge essential to teaching up to senior secondary level;
(2)  |  an understanding of mathematical literacy
which is considered to have desirable practical outcomes for the teaching of
mathematics in both primary and secondary sectors;
(3)  |  the communication and pedagogical skills
expected of teachers of mathematics;
(4)  |  an understanding of mathematical concepts and
theories and their application in teaching mathematics;
(5)  |  the ability to formulate and solve practical
problems mathematically;
(6)  |  the ability to critically analyse current
approaches and methods in mathematics education;
(7)  |  an ability to understand research topics on
teaching and learning of mathematics;
(8)  |  pedagogical content knowledge in teaching
mathematics;
(9)  |  practical skills in using textbooks and other
teaching resources and evaluation of learning outcomes;
(10)  |  a capability of establishing intellectual
development with an emphasis on analytical and problem-solving skills;
(11)  |  an appreciation of the contribution of
mathematics to the formation and improvement of human society;
(12)  |  an interest and an appreciation of
professional values of an educator.
